On 06/27/2011 02&#58;38 PM, Open Science Grid FootPrints wrote&#58;
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; [Duplicate message snipped]</font></pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='10532#1309199927'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2011-06-27T18:38:47+00:00">Jun 27, 2011 06:38 PM UTC</time> by <b>Christopher Pipes</b><a class="anchor" name="1309199927">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>Steve,

Since the problem has been identified, there is a work-around in place and the developers have been notified of the issue, may we consider this issues resolved for now?

Regards,
Christopher</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='10532#1309190197'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2011-06-27T15:56:37+00:00">Jun 27, 2011 03:56 PM UTC</time><a class="anchor" name="1309190197">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>Here&#39;s the update&#58;
We now understand the nature of the bug.  If there are &#62;120 groups in the HostToGroup mapping, then
no current browser can work to successfully submit that form to the current apache/tomcat/gums combo.
It is possible to work around this using the &#34;shortcut&#34; feature of GUMS that creates
all of the pieces at once and that&#39;s what we are doing now.

We do not want to enable the insecure renegotation feature on our Apache server and we don&#39;t think
anyone else should have to either.. so long term we are requesting the combination of GUMS developers
and VDT to identify some combination that makes it possible to securely add a HostToGroup without
enabling SSL insecure renegotiation on the server side.  this could either take the form
of reworking the JavaScript on that screen to not be sending so incredibly much data, or
identifying a new client which can securely send that big of an SSL payload in a GET statement.

Steve Timm

-- by Steve Timm</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='10532#1308341767'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2011-06-17T20:16:07+00:00">Jun 17, 2011 08:16 PM UTC</time> by <b>Christopher Pipes</b><a class="anchor" name="1308341767">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>Are there any updates on this issue? What do we do from here?

