On Mon Jun 06 17&#58;18&#58;08 2011, GOC wrote&#58;
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; [by Steve Timm]</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; Please assign this ticket to VDT support center&#58;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; The following problem occurs with versions of VDT Apache of 2.2.15</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; or greater (VDT 2.0.0p17 and later), and GUMS 1.3.17.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; When trying to add groups to a GUMS HostToGroup Mapping via the GUMS</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; WEB UI,</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; and if you have a HostToGroup Mapping which already contains 132 or</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; more GroupToAccountMappings, the following error is obtained</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; 413</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; Request Entity Too Large</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; The requested resource</font>
<div id='show_1397902042' class=''><button class="btn">Show More</button></div><div class='detail hidden' id='detail_1397902042'><font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; /gums/hostToGroupMappings.jsp</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; does not allow request data with GET requests, or the amount of data</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; provided in the request exceeds the capacity limit</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; (Note, if there are just 120 GroupToAccount mappings in the HostToGroup</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; Mapping, this error doesn&#39;t happen.  Note also, it doesn&#39;t matter if</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; you are trying to add a group or delete a group, the problem is the</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; same,</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; in fact if you just do two group changes and don&#39;t even hit save, the</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; problem is the same.)</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; John Hover, the GUMS developer, identified this as an issue with</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; SSLInsecureRenegotiation being disabled.  Apparently according to the</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; VDT release notes this patch (apache 2.2.15) was put in with</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; vdt-2.0.0p17</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; and greater.  that patch makes very large GET requests via SSL</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; such as the HostToGroup form fail.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; The Apache release notes say that with a new enough client, one which is</font>
