        </script></pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='10532#1307395534'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2011-06-06T21:25:34+00:00">Jun 6, 2011 09:25 PM UTC</time> by <b>OSG-GOC</b><a class="anchor" name="1307395534">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>[by Steve Timm]

Please assign this ticket to VDT support center&#58;

The following problem occurs with versions of VDT Apache of 2.2.15
or greater (VDT 2.0.0p17 and later), and GUMS 1.3.17.

When trying to add groups to a GUMS HostToGroup Mapping via the GUMS WEB UI,
and if you have a HostToGroup Mapping which already contains 132 or
more GroupToAccountMappings, the following error is obtained

413
Request Entity Too Large
The requested resource
/gums/hostToGroupMappings.jsp
does not allow request data with GET requests, or the amount of data provided in the request exceeds the capacity limit

(Note, if there are just 120 GroupToAccount mappings in the HostToGroup Mapping, this error doesn&#39;t happen.  Note also, it doesn&#39;t matter if
you are trying to add a group or delete a group, the problem is the same,
in fact if you just do two group changes and don&#39;t even hit save, the problem is the same.)

John Hover, the GUMS developer, identified this as an issue with SSLInsecureRenegotiation being disabled.  Apparently according to the
VDT release notes this patch (apache 2.2.15) was put in with vdt-2.0.0p17
and greater.  that patch makes very large GET requests via SSL
such as the HostToGroup form fail.

The Apache release notes say that with a new enough client, one which is
compiled against openssl 0.9.8m or greater, such GETS can work again.
Firefox 3.6 is evidently not such a client. Is the VDT aware of any such client?
We would prefer not to turn on the SSLInsecureRenegotiation on
feature in httpd-ssl.conf if we can.

Steve Timm</pre></div><legend>Similar Recent Tickets <small>modified within the last 30 days</small></legend><div id="similar_tickets"><p class="muted">No similar tickets found.</p></div>
